history</ref> |- |1989 || [[Charles Wadsworth]] || |- |1993 || [[Robert Merrill]], [[Arthur Mitchell (dancer)|Arthur Mitchell]] || |- |1997 || [[Skitch Henderson]] (1918&ndash;2005) ||<ref>[[Press release]] (December 8, 1997). [http://www.nyc.gov/html/om/html/97/sp722-97.html "Mayor Presents Handel Medallion to Skitch Henderson&nbsp;&ndash; Founder of New York Pops Receives City's Highest Cultural Award"]. [[Mayor of New York City]]'s Press Office. Retrieved October 11, 2011.</ref> |- |1999 || [[Merce Cunningham]] || |- |2002 || [[Licia Albanese]], [[Roberta Peters]] || |- |2011 || [[Stephen Sondheim]] || <ref>{{cite news| url=http://artsbeat.blogs.nytimes.com/2011/10/10/sondheim-to-receive-new-york-city-arts-honor/?scp=2&sq=sondheim&st=cse | work=The New York Times | first=Patricia | last=Cohen | title=Sondheim to Receive New York City Arts Honor | date=October 10, 2011}}</ref> |}
