[[Law]] in Oceania refers to the different legal systems within the geographical area of Oceania. Countries such as [[Australia]] and [[New Zealand]] follow in the [[Commonwealth of Nations|Commonwealth]] tradition of common law, and until recently were subject to the United Kingdom [[House of Lords]]. Other countries and islands trace their legal heritage to different former colonialists.

